Clare Hines was diagnosed with a brain tumour after suffering epileptic seizures  . 
  She was told she had to have surgery to remove the benign tumour or terminate her unborn baby . 
  One week before surgery she found out she was pregnant  . 
  She decided to keep the baby and give birth to her son Noah . 
  She suffered three seizures during labour . 
  Ms Hines had surgery to have the tumour removed in the UK . 
  She had suffered another seizure after returning to Australia . 
 